.TH "gen_pool_dma_zalloc" 9 "gen_pool_dma_zalloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_pool_dma_zalloc \- allocate special zeroed memory from the pool for DMA usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" gen_pool_dma_zalloc
.BI "(struct gen_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool to allocate from
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to allocate from the pool
.IP "dma" 12
dma-view physical address return value.  Use NULL if unneeded.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate the requested number of zeroed bytes from the specified pool.
Uses the pool allocation function (with first-fit algorithm by default).
Can not be used in NMI handler on architectures without
NMI-safe cmpxchg implementation.
.SH "RETURN"
virtual address of the allocated zeroed memory, or NULL on failure
